snippet: A reorganization plan for Milwaukee’s Roman Catholic archdiocese that will distribute $21 million to hundreds of clergy sex abuse victims won approval Monday from a federal bankruptcy judge.
abstract: Federal bankruptcy Judge Susan Kelley approves reorganization plan for Milwaukee’s Roman Catholic archdiocese that will distribute $21 million to hundreds of victims who were sexually abused by clergy.
lead_paragraph: A reorganization plan for Milwaukee’s Roman Catholic archdiocese that will distribute $21 million to hundreds of clergy sex abuse victims won approval Monday from a federal bankruptcy judge.

headline.main: Wisconsin: Bankruptcy Plan Settles Abuse Claims
headline.print_headline: Wisconsin: Bankruptcy Plan Settles Abuse Claims
